A N A C T
RELATING TO PUBLIC UTILITIES AND CARRIERS -- REGULATORY POWERS OF
ADMINISTRATION
Introduced By: Representatives Kazarian, Dawson, DeSimone, Voas, Alzate, Stewart,
Edwards, Morales, Furtado, and Casimiro
Date Introduced: February 26, 2025
Referred To: House Corporations
It is enacted by the General Assembly as follows:
1
2 SECTION 1. Chapter 39-3 of the General Laws entitled "Regulatory Powers of
3 Administration" is hereby amended by adding thereto the following section:
4 39-3-11.4. Internet access rates for seniors.
5 (a) For purposes of this section, "Internet" means collectively the myriad of computer and
6 telecommunications facilities, including equipment and operating software, that comprise the
7 interconnected worldwide network of networks that employ the transmission control
8 protocol/Internet protocol, or any predecessor or successor protocols, to such protocol, to
9 communicate information of all kinds by wire or radio.
10 (b) Effective January 1, 2026, providers of access to the Internet shall not increase rates for
11 persons sixty-two (62) years or older for connection services to the Internet.
12 SECTION 2. This act shall take effect upon passage.
